ily:algerian;font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Tavern Heroes</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:algerian;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>you need to:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
- Be level 50+<br>
- Know or be willing to learn how to effectively contribute to your group (ie., assist correctly),<br>
- Like to play in a family and help others (We Guild group A LOT),<br>
- Enjoy challenges,<br>
- Remember raiding has little to do with any loot that may drop (unless for an Epic) ,but is mainly for the challenge and fun that comes with it. (Translation, if your a greedy bastard; DO NOT APPLY.  If you beg, DO NOT APPLY)<br>
<br>
Then, if you'd like to join us, you need to post on this board or contact a officer in game.<br>
When posting here, please include the following information:<br>
- your name and surname<br>
- level<br>
- AA's<br>
- class<br>
- any keys or flags you have obtained<br>
- Epic status<br>
- and a small explanation why you wish to join us<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:algerian;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>As a Candidate</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
This is the probationary period of your enlistment into Tavern Heroes. During these 2 to 3 weeks, you will wear the guild tag, but you will not have access to the private section of our website until you become a full member. You will be able to and are expected to follow the guild in all raids or groups. At this time, you will not participate in the lotto during raids. We do a lot of guild groups every week to help folks, visit places or just gain Xp. During this period all of the officers will try to get to know you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:algerian;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>One of the Family</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
At the end of your candidate period, you will be formally interviewed by the Guild Leader or one of the officers other than your sponsor. Your full membership will go to a board, and upon approval, you will be welcomed as one of the Heroes. <br>
Once inducted, you will be given access to the private section of the website (which we need members to visit at least 3 times a week), and be entered into the lotto during raids.<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Remember that it is your personal responsibility to uphold the ideals of our guild, now more than ever.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:algerian;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>What can make the process faster?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
The speed at which you become a full member, will always be at the discretion of the board, but will not take longer than 3 weeks.<br>
Things that might help in making it shorter than 3 weeks:<br>
- We have known you for a long time<br>
- You have participated in groups or raids with us prior to becoming interested in joining us<br>
- Have a sponser, meaning you know and play with someone already in the guild.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">The more we see of you, the quicker we will all get to know you.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:algerian;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Questions?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Send one of the Officers a tell in game.<br>
<br>
